{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In two recent papers focusing specifically on empathy, providing people with the information that an empathic response was produced by AI compared to humans led to a significant reduction in empathy (Rubin et al., 2025; Yin et al., 2024).",
    "Further work extended these findings, suggesting that people appreciated emotional support more when the supporter expressed emotion, but no differences between human and AI labels were found when focused on cognitive aspects of emotional support (Rubin et al., 2025).",
    "One interesting question is whether label differences are unique to empathy or extend to other, more cognitive strategies such as reappraisal.",
    "Finally, one important factor in the differences between human and AI reappraisal is differences in language use.",
    "It's possible that AI reappraisal is perceived to be better merely because of the complexity of language."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In two recent papers focusing specifically on empathy, providing people with the information that an empathic response was produced by AI compared to humans led to a significant reduction in empathy (Rubin et al., 2025; Yin et al., 2024).",
    "Further work extended these findings, suggesting that people appreciated emotional support more when the supporter expressed emotion, but no differences between human and AI labels were found when focused on cognitive aspects of emotional support (Rubin et al., 2025)."
  ]
